text: Andreas Kempf (March 14, 1881 - March 29, 1963) was an American gymnast. He competed in three events at the 1904 Summer Olympics in Missouri. ==References== Category:1881 births Category:1963 deaths Category:American male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of the United States Category:Gymnasts at the 1904 Summer Olympics Category:People from Basel-Stadt
